</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Little colored spots (size of a pixel) in unprinted area 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Only seen in C1630, C1650 and M-series 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> All colors are present 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Pixels only seen with a microscope 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-2A8DB0E9-AD7B-4A1A-BC8A-B74F6A432399" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Functional Logging (if available)</title><p class="- topic/p ">No logging available 
</p></section><section id="GUID-E15DB02C-1EE8-4A31-A08D-08EB93AF1BFA" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">ADAM-triggers</title><p class="- topic/p ">No ADAM-triggers available. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-DDCC1BB0-B402-4010-9156-67DB737F3DE5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Analyze/Repair</title><p class="- topic/p "> Not applicable 
</p></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p "> Release 2 ink may dry out in case a nozzle has not been used for a while. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">To prevent this each nozzles is kept in shape by splitting some droplets in unprinted areas. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This spitting is done by every color and is performed by every unused nozzle. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The droplets are randomly spread over the media and so small they cannot be seen by the naked eye. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In the C1640 other ink is used which doesn't show this drying out. Therefor the spitting is only active in the C1630, C1650 and M-series. 
</p><note id="GUID-651D5E30-DCE2-4CE2-AA5B-567A57F82B0D" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> When using a white printmode in the M-series, these spots are not present anymore because the spitbar is used besides the print. Spitting in the print is not done when printing white.
</p></note></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-945E6C60-1212-47DF-9487-92374227D4B4.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
